      %h2
        Product Manager
        %a{:name => 'product-manager'} &nbsp;
      San Francisco

      = tapjoy_overview

      %p We offer an opportunity to help build the largest mobile publishing company in the world &ndash; this Product Manager will play a key role in contributing to Tapjoy's financial and industry success.

      %p
        %strong Role and Responsibilities
      %p We are seeking a Product Manager who will take ownership of all internal and publisher facing tools for our Web business. This role will interface heavily with sales, ad operations, and game developers.
      %ul
        %li Work cross-functionally to translate requests from developers, sales, and ad operations into product requirements.
        %li Work with engineering, QA and customer support to identify issues and develop solutions.
        %li Work closely with customers to capture product feedback, respond to issues and ensure customer success.
        %li Write requirements, create wireframes, and lead the product development process.
        %li Monitor progress of initiatives through the product development life cycle, identifying risks and opportunities and keeping stakeholders informed.

      %p
        %strong Professional Experience and Personal Qualities
      %ul
        %li 1-2 years of product management experience managing internal tools and reporting, with some previous customer interaction
        %li Prior experience working with onshore and offshore development teams is highly desired
        %li Exceptional interpersonal skills, including the ability to communicate with technical and business teams. The ability to receive feedback and prioritize the most important tasks effectively.
        %li Experience working with, maintaining, and improving a legacy reporting system/tools would be very helpful
        %li Strong self-motivation and an ability to get things done
        %li Experience communicating successfully with external clients
        %li Experience and excitement for working in a fast-paced environment
        %li Strong organizational skills and attention to detail with proven experience managing projects to successful completion
        %li Undergraduate degree in a relevant discipline
        %li High capacity, able to operate effectively in turbulent environment

